**1\. Description of the Application**

The Class Schedule Tracker is a web-based application designed to help students, beadles, and professors manage class attendance efficiently. The system allows students to register their schedules and receive automated reminders via SMS through Twilio before each class. Beadles can log attendance digitally, while professors can generate cut-class reports. The application streamlines documentation and ensures accountability across all users.

**2\.  Controller Operations**

| Operation Name | REST URL | Method | Parameters | Input | Output | Error Messages | Forwards to |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| Add Class Schedule | /schedule/add | POST | None | { studentId, classId, dayofweek, startTime, endTime, location } | { “status”: “success”, “message”: “Schedule added” } | 400 Bad Request 404 Not Found | Student Component → addStudentProfile() |
| Get Today’s Schedule and Send Reminder | /schedule/reminder | GET | Phone (Optional query param) | None | { “status”: “success”, “message”: Reminder sent”, “classes”: \[...\] } | 401 Unauthorized  500 Server Error | Messaging Component → queueMessage() → sendSMS()  |
| Log Attendance Entry | /attendance/log | POST | None | { attendanceId, studentId, status } | { “status”: “success”, “message”: “Attendance logged” } | 400 Bad Request 403 Forbidden | Beadle Component → logAttendance() → Attendance Component → createAttendanceRecord()  |
| View Cut Classes Report | /attendance/cut-report{classId} | GET | classId (path variable) | None | { “classId”: 1010, “students”: \[...\] } | 404 Not Found  403 Forbidden | Attendance Component → getListOfPresentStudents() → Professor Component → generateCutReport()  |
| Register Student | /register/student | POST  | studentId, name, phoneNumber  |  | { "status":"success", "message":"Student registered" }  | 400 Bad Request  | Student Component → addStudentProfile()  |
| Register Beadle | /register/beadle | POST  | idNumber, name, phoneNumber, classProfile(optional)  |  | { "status":"success", "message":"Beadle registered" } | 400 Bad Request  | Beadle Component → switchUserProfile()  |

**3\. Components and Their Responsibilities**

* ### **Student Component**

  * addStudentProfile() – stores student registration info.  
  * receiveMessage() – triggered when Twilio sends SMS to student.

* ### **Scheduler Component**

  * checkUpcomingClasses() – scans for classes starting within 10 minutes.  
  * sendClassReminder() – hands off details to the Messaging Component.  
  * retrieveAttendanceReport() – provides attendance summary.

* ### **Beadle Component**

  * logAttendance() – records present students and returns attendancePK.

* ### **Attendance Component**

  * createAttendanceRecord() – stores attendance linked to schedule/date.  
  * getListOfPresentStudents() – returns students that attended.

* ### **Professor Component**

  * viewAttendance() – displays logged attendance after class.  
  * generateCutReport() – identifies students who cut.

* ### **Messaging Component**

  * queueMessage(studentPhone, classDetails) – prepares SMS.  
  * sendSMS() – sends SMS through Twilio.

**4\. Entities and Repositories**

## Student

This entity represents a student within a class.

| Data | Type | Null? | Validation |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| StudentPK | Long | NonNull | Self-Generated |
| IDNumber | String | NonNull | Length \= 6 |
| Name | String | NonNull | N/A |
| phoneNumber | String | NonNull | Regex: \+639XXXXXXXXX |

## Attendance Entry

This entity represents an entry for an attendance entity. For all intents and purposes, this is an Associative Entity meant to aid in database normalization. In this instance, this tracks the student's attendance.

| Data | Type | Null? | PK? | Validation |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| StudentPK | Long | NonNull | Y | From Student |
| AttendancePK | Long | NonNull | Y | From Attendance |
| AttendanceStatus | String | NonNull | N | Either one of the following: Attended Late Missed Classes |

## 

## Attendance

This entity represents the list of attendants for a particular day.

| Data | Type | Null? | PK? | Validation |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| AttendancePK | Long | NonNull | Y | Self-Generated |
| ClassPK | String | NonNull | Y, FK | From Class |
| BeadlePK | String | NonNull | Y, FK | N/A |
| Date | Date | NonNull | N | Date |

## 

## 

## Beadle

This entity represents the Beadle of a class. The beadle is the primary person checking attendance.

| Data | Type | Null? | Validation |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| BeadlePK | Long | NonNull | Self-Generated |
| idNumber | String | NonNull | Length \= 6 |
| Name | String | NonNull | N/A |
| phoneNumber | String | NonNull | Regex: \+639XXXXXXXXX |

## Class

This entity represents the subject class.

| Data | Type | Null? | PK | Validation |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| ClassPK | Long | NonNull | Y | Self-Generated |
| BeadlePK | Long | NonNull | N, FK | From BeadlePK |
| Class Name | String | NonNull | N | N/A |
| Professor Name | String | NonNull | N | N/A |
| Time | TIME | NonNull | N | Formatted as XX:XX:XX, following mysql standards. |

# Repositories

1. AttendanceEntryRepository  
- findByAttendancePK(Long PK) \- used to help generate the attendance report for the Attendance Component  
- findByAttendanceStatus(String status) \- used to filter by the status of the student. Will require additional filtering by attendancePK.  
2. StudentRepository  
- findByStudent(Long PK) \- standard student retrieval method for general use  
3. ClassRepository  
- findByTime(String Time) \- Meant to be used for the scheduler component
